==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lither
<hw>Li"ther</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧"⟦th⟧⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>l⟦ymac⟧⟦edh⟧er</ets> bad, wicked.]</ety> <def>Bad; wicked; false;
worthless; slothful.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not <qex>lither</qex> in business, fervent in spirit.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Woolton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Professor Skeat thinks ⟦ldquo⟧ the <xex>lither</xex>
sky⟦rdquo⟧ as found in Shakespeare's Henry VI. ((Part I. IV. VII., 21)
means the stagnant or pestilential sky.</note></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Li"ther*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>. -- <wf>Li"ther*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Litherly</ent>⟦br⟧
